I’m 40 thousand feet in the air on my way to Dubai — enjoying a nice glass of wine. & I can’t help but reflect on when this dream of mine to become a pro bike rider seemed so unrealistic. 14 years of blood, sweat, and tears has brought me to this place of gratitude. The vision is only getting bigger. I say all of this to say, believe in yourself, work hard, & stay true to your process. Good things take time. Let’s keep building 🫶🏾 - JB

I’ve been creating content since I was 13 with a little handycam that my mom bought me (thanks Mom). A decade later, I’m partnering with the world’s largest independent lens manufacturer, @sigmaphoto, to tell my story as a creative 🤯 

I’ve been fortunate enough to travel the world on my BMX bike. What better place to collaborate with SIGMA than their hometown?! 

For the people asking what I shoot my content with – I use a Sony A6500 with the SIGMA F1.4 DC DN | Contemporary lenses. This compact setup has been the perfect travel companion. Light, sharp & amazing in low light with its F1.4 aperture 📷

Here are some self-portraits I shot last month at the Tokyo Tower 😎 

#LifeOnTwoWheels #SigmaAmbassador

I picked up a camera to document my journey through my own POV. Partnering with a brand like @sigmaphoto is only more motivation to continue telling my story through the content I create 

Here is some BTS of the self-portraits I shot at the Tokyo Tower. The goal was to use the whole range of SIGMA F1.4 DC DN | Contemporary lenses 📸

Drop any questions you have about these lenses in the comments & we’ll answer them!! #lifeontwowheels #SigmaAmbassador
